👋 **Hi there!** I’ve run some quick measurements against master and your PR. These metrics should help the humans reviewing this PR gauge whether it might negatively affect compile times or editor responsiveness for users who install these typings. Let’s review the numbers, shall we? These typings are for a package that doesn’t yet exist on master, so I don’t have anything to compare against yet! In the future, I’ll be able to compare PRs to es-abstract with its source on master.

<!--footer bot @ 10/22/2019, 3:31:54 PM footerend-->
These types are still very much a work in progress.

Also, it’s likely that I’ll soon have to update this to v2.0 because of https://github.com/ljharb/es-abstract/issues/62, https://github.com/ljharb/es-abstract/issues/66, https://github.com/ljharb/es-abstract/pull/67, https://github.com/ljharb/es-abstract/pull/68 and https://github.com/ljharb/es-abstract/pull/69.
I wouldn't wait for v2; it'd be more useful to get v1.17 out.

@ExE-Boss Thank you for submitting this PR! 


## Code Reviews

This PR adds a new definition, so it needs to be reviewed by a DT maintainer before it can be merged.

- [es-abstract on npm](https://www.npmjs.com/package/es-abstract)
 - [es-abstract on unpkg](https://unpkg.com/browse/es-abstract@latest//)

## Status

 * ✅ No merge conflicts
 * ✅ Continuous integration tests have passed
 * ❌ Only a DT maintainer can approve changes when there are new packages added

Once every item on this list is checked, I'll ask you for permission to merge and publish the changes.
